title: How Russian disinformation toppled government after government in Africa
description: In the two years since an Israelis company first tried to thwart a Russian disinformation campaign in Burkina Faso, coups or rebels have removed the governments of five former French colonies, replacing them with pro-Russia leaders.

title: SEC: SolarWinds failed to disclose cybersecurity woes before historic breach
description: SolarWinds suffered a historic breach that made waves in 2020, and now the Securities and Exchange Commission is taking action against the company and its CISO Tim Brown.

title: Under prosecution’s fire, Sam Bankman-Fried brushes off past comments
description: The disgraced ex-mogul and founder of FTX tried to distance himself from the statements he made while his crypto exchange imploded.

title: Google CEO calls search ‘very competitive’ in defending Apple deal
description: Google’s CEO Sundar Pichai appeared Monday as the star witness for Google’s defense against a landmark antitrust case.

title: Scams are targeting teenagers. Here’s how to keep your kids safe.
description: Even kids who grew up online need to learn about scams and fraud. Here’s how parents can prepare them for the worst the internet has to offer.

title: Biden to sign sweeping artificial intelligence executive order
description: President Biden is expected to sign a sweeping artificial intelligence executive order on Monday, marking the U.S.’s most ambitious regulatory attempt yet.
